issue.title: A question about week-06
issue.body:
# Week-06
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/42177490/45799200-423fb380-bcdf-11e8-93d3-4683d4fa2c3f.png)
In this part of week-06, it shows "by_link_text". But only when I change it to "by_partial_link_text", can it works.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/42177490/45799347-c3974600-bcdf-11e8-9934-ec58c5fd05df.png)
I am confused about when should we use "partial".

comment.body:
> @Catmint1215 Good question, I think this is because the link text is changing in Google search. I will update in the notes.
> 
> Basically, you can tell the difference by their names.
> `link_text`: it returns elements with an **exact** match of the given text.
> `partial_link_text`: returns elements which **include** the given text.
> 
> For the example we demo, except the text we search, there is some extra words `An ...`
> ![find-text-link-by-partiallinktext](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37010763/45809874-e6cfee80-bcfb-11e8-973e-cdbc19d7a6b7.jpg)
> Thats the reason why you cannot find the elements in the precise match mode.



> @Catmint1215 Good question, I think this is because the link text is changing in Google search. I will update in the notes.
> 
> Basically, you can tell the difference by their names.
> `link_text`: it returns elements with an **exact** match of the given text.
> `partial_link_text`: returns elements which **include** the given text.
> 
> For the example we demo, except the text we search, there is some extra words `An ...`
> ![find-text-link-by-partiallinktext](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37010763/45809874-e6cfee80-bcfb-11e8-973e-cdbc19d7a6b7.jpg)
> Thats the reason why you cannot find the elements in the precise match mode.

Thanks a lot! 师兄~

issue.title: Install Python3 on Windows and Set Environment
issue.body:
1. Click [here](https://www.python.org/ftp/python/3.7.0/python-3.7.0.exe) to download Python 3.7.
2. Remember to choose 'Customize installation' and click 'pip' when you are installing python. If you install the default version, you cannot import 'numpy' module in week2. 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/42831899/45255308-2111c580-b3b7-11e8-8371-82c3b687956d.png)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/42831899/45255309-253de300-b3b7-11e8-94b8-47f622ece7f9.png)

comment.body: If you still can not download it, I can send the ".exe" to you directly.
